Title : Scott E. Friedman
Text : '''Scott E. Friedman''' (born September 17, 1958) is an American author and attorney from [[Buffalo, New York]]. Since 2009 he has been the managing partner of the Buffalo law firm Lippes Mathias Wexler Friedman LLP.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/01/your-money/the-ethical-will-an-ancient-concept-is-revamped-for-the-tech-age.html?_r=0 "The Ethical Will, an Ancient Concept, Is Revamped for the Tech Age"]. ''New York Times'', Nov 1, 2014. Constance Gustke</ref> Friedman writes and speaks about the effect of positive psychology on the successful operation of family-run businesses.<ref name="Lyon2003">{{cite book|author=Elizabeth Lyon|title=Writer's Guide to Nonfiction|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6M5Zidq9bTkC&pg=PA49|date=4 March 2003|publisher=Penguin|isbn=978-1-101-15350-5|pages=49–}}</ref> He is the author of seven books, five of which cover this topic.

== Early life and education ==
Friedman was born in [[Williamsville, New York]]. He is a graduate of [[Trinity College (Connecticut)|Trinity College]] where he earned his BA. He went on to study at [[Washington University School of Law]], earning his J.D. Friedman then attended the [[University of Pennsylvania School of Law]], earning his LLM.<ref name=scanlon>[http://buffalonews.com/2016/09/10/lawyer-scott-friedman-helps-shepherd-medical-breakthroughs-to-market/ "Lawyer Scott Friedman helps shepherd medical breakthroughs to market"]. ''Buffalo News'',  By Scott Scanlon September 10, 2016</ref>

== Career == 
As a young man Friedman worked at a law firm in Philadelphia.<ref name=scanlon/> In 2009 he became the Managing Partner of Lippes Mathias Wexler Friedman LLP in Buffalo.<ref>[http://www.buffalonews.com/business/lippes-mathias-law-firm-to-move-into-key-center-20150630 "Lippes Mathias law firm to move into Key Center"]. ''Buffalo News'', By Stephen T. Watson | News Staff Reporter on June 30, 2015  </ref><ref name=salamander>[http://www.buffalonews.com/business/salamander-skin-for-surgery-repairs-a-group-of-buffalo-investors-thinks-so-20160129 "Salamander skin for surgery repairs? A group of Buffalo investors thinks so"]. By Stephen T. Watson | ''Buffalo News'', January 29, 2016</ref>  His work at the firm involves helping health care businesses operate efficiently and avoid legal tangles.<ref name=scanlon />

Friedman has been frequently interviewed as an expert in family business planning.<ref>[http://www.bizjournals.com/buffalo/print-edition/2013/05/24/attorney-combines-science-law-to-help.html "Attorney combines science, law to help family businesses"]. ''Buffalo Business First''. May 24, 2013.</ref> He has also authored several articles on the subject for state and national publications. In June, 2013 he wrote a feature for ''Family Business Magazine'', titled "A scientific field offers insights for family businesses."

Friedman serves on the board of directors of the biotech company Photolitech.<ref>[http://buffalonews.com/2015/03/04/roswell-park-spinoff-indian-pharma-company-start-joint-venture/ "Roswell Park spinoff, Indian pharma company start joint venture"]. ''Buffalo News'',  By Stephen T. Watson, Mar 4, 2015</ref> In 2014 he organized the investment group Buffalo Capital Partners.<ref>[http://buffalonews.com/2016/01/29/salamander-skin-for-surgery-repairs-a-group-of-buffalo-investors-thinks-so/ "Salamander skin for surgery repairs? A group of Buffalo investors thinks so"]. ''Buffalo News'',  By Stephen T. Watson, Jan 29, 2016</ref><ref>[http://www.bizjournals.com/buffalo/news/2015/08/25/buffalo-business-leaders-form-venture-capital.html "Buffalo business leaders form venture capital group"]. ''Buffalo Business First'', Aug 25, 2015. Dan Miner </ref>

In 2015 Friedman gave a series of talks related to investment and startup companies.<ref>[http://www.buffalonews.com/business/on-the-record/on-the-record-oct-6-2015-20151005 "On the Record: Oct. 6, 2015"]. ''Buffalo News'', on October 5, 2015</ref> In 2016 he is one of several investors involved in the firm Buffalo Capital.<ref name=salamander /> That year he became a member of the Council for the State University of New York at Buffalo.<ref>[http://www.buffalonews.com/business/business-people/business-people-for-the-week-of-aug-7-20160807 "Business People for the week of Aug. 7 "]. ''Buffalo News'', August 7, 2016</ref>

== Books ==
Friedman has written seven books drawing on his work as an attorney. He co-authored his first books related to family business with his brother Michael Friedman in 1994. The title, ''How to Run a Family Business'', was the first of five books Friedman authored focused on advising families on how to better operate their family business. Other books in the series are ''The Successful Family Business''<ref>[http://www.chicagobusiness.com/article/19971206/ISSUE01/10003872/communication-keeps-things-happy-healthy "COMMUNICATION KEEPS THINGS HAPPY, HEALTHY"]. Craine's Chicago Business'', December 06, 1997 By: Barbara B. Buchholz </ref> and ''Family Business and Positive Psychology''.<ref>[http://www.americanbar.org/publications/gpsolo_ereport/2014/april_2014/book_review_family_business_and_positive_psychology.html "Book Review: Family Business and Positive Psychology"]. ''GP Solo eReport'', Vol. 3, No. 9 American Bar Association. by Mike Hurley</ref>
 
== Honors and awards ==
Friedman has received numerous awards for his professional accomplishments. He has been named to Who’s Who in America.<ref>[http://www.marquiswhoswho.com/booksellers/publications/whos-who-in-american-law Who’s Who in American Law]</ref>

